aiyesinmi str; in Ikorodu, Lagos. He alleged that they defiled the 12-year-old girl. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of sections 411 and 137 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria. An Ikorodu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State, on Friday ordered that a 24-year-old applicant, Lateef Ola-Osebikan, who allegedly defiled an eight-year-old girl, be remanded in prison, pending legal advice. July 26, 2019 In "Crime Guard" An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos on Friday ordered that a 51-year-old man, Ukapi Agwu, who allegedly defiled a 13-year-old girl, be remanded in prison. May 19, 2019 In "News" An Ikeja Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday ordered that a 22-year-old conductor, Dapo Amakwe, who allegedly defiled and impregnated a 14-year-old girl, be remanded in prison, pending the receipt of legal advice.   The magistrate, Mrs B.O. Osunsanmi did not take the plea of the defendant.   Osunsanmi ordered the investigating police… October 2, 2019 In "News"